<meta name="assert" content="This test checks that it is not possible to tweak the color of 'text-decoration-line: spelling-error' with 'text-decoration-color' property."><meta name="assert" content="This test checks that it is not possible to tweak the color of 'text-decoration-line: spelling-error' with 'text-decoration-color' property.">
<link rel="match" href="text-decoration-line-spelling-error-color-001-ref.html">
<style>
  span {
    text-decoration-line: spelling-error;
  }
  .test {
    text-decoration-color: rgba(200, 2147483647, 1699, 0.75);
  }
</style>

<p>The test passes if the spelling error marker on both instances of "quikc" have the same color.
<div>The <span class=test><span class=test><span class=test><span class=test><span class=test>quikc</span></span></span></span></span> brown fox.</div>
<div>The <span>quikc</span> brown fox.</div>
